  "texts": [
    "For the valley wall, we thus expect a smoothly textured DW, with the width of the DW set by the valley stiffness and the gradient of the sublattice potential, ∆ max /w.",
    "On the other hand, there is a topological obstruction towards forming inter-Chern coherence [30] (see discussion in Section 4) and thus the Chern wall is sharp.",
    "This leads to the following energetic competition reflected in the numerics in Fig. 9b: For small ∆ max /w, the valley wall can texture and thereby reduce the exchange energy loss compared to the Chern wall, so that the valley wall has lower energy.",
    "For large ∆ max /w, the valley wall becomes sharp and does not benefit from any texturing.",
    "In this regime, the Chern DW is lower in energy."
